race.comment: Absolute lottery. HELL (4) is a genuine sprinter who led all the way to win with a bit to spare last time out over today's journey at Eagle Farm. Up in class and has to do some early work from a wide gate but he is impossible to rule out in any six-furlong contest. MISTER BIANCO (9) led for the judge but tanked at the end over 1400m recently. The winner of three from six at this trip. Rodd replaces a 3kg claimer so plenty to like about his chances. JONNY DA WOLF (14) returned in good order over 1000m last start. Placed at Listed level at the close of last prep so he has the quality to test this field. BATTLEFIELD (5) off a six-week freshen up is in the mix with regular rider Robbie Dolan back aboard.
